{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1988 | theme = | logo = | final = 27 February 1988 | presenters = [[Bengt Grafström]] | winner = "[[Stad i ljus]]" by [[Tommy Körberg]] | vote = Regional juries | host = | venue = [[Malmö Stadsteater]], [[Malmö]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1988''' was the selection for the 28th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 27th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 1,100 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT2|TV2]] and was not broadcast on radio. The show was watched by 4,464,000 people.
