{{Infobox NRHP | name = Vurpillat's Opera House | nrhp_type = | image = Vurpillat's Opera House Winimac Indiana P1300091.jpg | caption = Vurpillat's Opera House, n.d. | location= Jct. of Market and Main Sts., [[Winamac, Indiana]] | coordinates = {{coord|41|3|4|N|86|36|15|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Indiana#USA | built = {{Start date|1883}} | architect = Rhodes, James | builder = Vurpillat, Frank | architecture = Second Empire | added = March 20, 2002 | area = less than one acre | refnum = 02000201<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
'''Vurpillat's Opera House''' is a historic [[opera house]] located at [[Winamac, Indiana|Winamac]], [[Pulaski County, Indiana]]. It was built in 1883, and is a three-story, ractangular, [[Second Empire architecture|Second Empire]] style brick building with a [[mansard roof]]. It sits on a [[limestone]] foundation and features metal decorative details.<ref name="SHAARD">{{cite web| url = https://secure.in.gov/apps/dnr/shaard/welcome.html| title = Indiana State Historic Architectural and Archaeological Research Database (SHAARD) | publisher = Department of Natural Resources, Division of Historic Preservation and Archaeology | format = Searchable database| accessdate = 2016-06-01}} ''Note:'' This includes {{cite web| url =https://secure.in.gov/apps/dnr/shaard/r/23555/N/Vurpillats_Opera_House_Pulaski_CO_Nom.pdf| title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Vurpillat's Opera House| accessdate = 2016-06-01| author=Lynda Irving| format = PDF| date=January 2001}} and Accompanying photographs.</ref>{{rp|5}}
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2002.<ref name=nris/>
